blueprint_book.label: Rail for Stations
blueprint_book.description: Loops for train stations, exactly wide enough to fit the requester/provider station blueprints side by side.

blueprint.description:
Parameters can be adjusted via the control combinator if necessary.
- Item request type
- [virtual-signal=signal-R] stacks of item to request
- [virtual-signal=signal-S] request stack threshold (deficit required to send a train)
- [virtual-signal=signal-L] train limit
- [virtual-signal=signal-P] station priority (out of 100, default 50)
- [virtual-signal=signal-1] - [virtual-signal=signal-5] network (circuit type sets network)

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: Check if more allowable trains are needed.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description: Convert the additonal train signal to the request item.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description: Takes the difference between the number of trains needed and the number of trains on the way.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
Negate the request signal for request management.
Pushes signal to green global network.

entities.name: selector-combinator
entities.player_description:
Set the quality of the request signal to push it to the correct train network.
Pushes signal to red global network.

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: Filters the priority signal to send to the train stop.

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: Set indicator lamp to yellow when trains are on the way but not at the station.

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: Set indicator lamp to blue when a train is at the station.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description: Find the average item count for a chest in the station, negated, for balanced unloading.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description: Calculate Threshold Amount.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description: Calculate Request Amount.

entities.name: constant-combinator
entities.player_description:
Control combinator
- [item=parameter-0] Requested Item
- [virtual-signal=signal-R] Request Stack Amount
- [virtual-signal=signal-S] Request Stack Threshold
- [virtual-signal=signal-L] Train Limit
- [virtual-signal=signal-P] Priority
- [virtual-signal=signal-1] - [virtual-signal=signal-5] Network

entities.name: selector-combinator
entities.player_description: Obtain stack size of requested item.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
Calculate deficit
(Ra - I)

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Is the deficit greater than the threshold?
IF (Ra - I) > Rt
SEND (Ra - I)

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
Calculate required trains.
K = (Ra - I) / F

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description: Calculate the number of items summoned by K trains.

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: If K is less than the necessary number of trains to fill the request, add 1 to the signal.

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: Set the train limit when the station needs more trains than the limit.

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: Set the train limit when the station needs less trains than the limit.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description: Convert the T signal to the L signal sent to the station.

blueprint_book.label: Frodo's Train Solutions [virtual-signal=signal-fuel-parameter]
blueprint_book.description:
Frodo's train-building system, including track and station layouts and a pseudo-LTN system for supply trains. Documentation is provided in blueprints where necessary.

Created by FrodobagginsTNT.

Changes in V4.1:
- improved train calling in an attempt to mitigate multiple trains being called for a single request. Still needs work.
- Cargo and fluid trains are now part of a train group by default.
